cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with LTL model-checking problems and stuttering theorem for Past LTL.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with flat counter systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses complexity results for different classes of flat counter systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper deals with arithmetical constraints on counters.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses complexity upper bounds for the LTL model-checking problem.
